# shadcn instructions

Use the latest version of Shadcn to install new components, like this command to add a button component:

```bash
pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add button
```

# drizzle entities and types

When creating new entities always add raw DB types (Select / Insert / Update) in `db/types.ts`.

# domain / view types

Composed types that extend or pick from DB types (e.g. with extra fields like `role`, nested relations, or picked subsets) belong in `src/types.ts`. Do NOT put them in the store or in component files.

# server functions

- All `createServerFn` calls live in `actions.ts` inside the corresponding component feature folder (e.g. `src/components/accounts/actions.ts`).
- Do not create or use `*.server.ts`, `actions.server.ts`, or route-level `action.ts` / `actions.ts` files.
- If a route needs server functions, move them into the matching component feature’s `actions.ts` and import them into the route.
- Plain async helper functions called only from within server handlers (e.g. `requireOwner`) also live in that same feature `actions.ts` file — no need to wrap them in `createServerFn`.

# standard components rules

1. If adding Delete component, use `entityId` prop instead of `entity` prop, do not pass the whole entity object.
